node.text:
Katie McRose, 26, and her wife Darian travel around Texas to sheer sheep, llamas and alpacas. They founded their business, Right Choice Shearing, in 2019. This year, they expect to bring in at least $80,000 servicing over 575 farms. 

Read more: https://cnb.cx/3AfkSJ2

node.title: Bringing in $80K a year shearing sheep in Texas.

node.text: This young couple earn $168,000 a year — here’s everything they spent in a week, including a 5-day vacation.

node.title: What A Family Making $168K Spends In A Week | Millennial Money

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Kathy Hochul set to become New York's first female governor after Cuomo resigns makeit'.

node.text:
Lt. Gov. Kathy Hochul is set to take over running the New York state government in two weeks from Gov. Andrew Cuomo, who announced his resignation because of a sexual harassment scandal. ⁠
⁠
Learn more about Hochul and read her statement following Cuomo's remarks at the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 10, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says '#makeit CNBC Make It @CNBCMakelt Interview prep: Tell us about yourself... only using emojis »makeit'.

node.text:
We'll go first: 💸✍️👩‍💻📱📈⁠
⁠
If you're in need of a little extra prep, we're sharing the best ways to answer 7 of the most common job interview questions at the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Remove these 7 things from your resume 'ASAP,' says CEO who has read more than 1,000 resumes this year RESUME az! - #makeit'.

node.text:
We constantly hear about what you should put on your resume, but we rarely talk about what to leave off.⁠
⁠
From too many soft skills to the wrong kind of email, head over to the link in our bio for a list of 7 things you should remove "ASAP," according to the CEO of a resume writing service.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'This 65-year-old retiree just moved into a $420 per month apartment in Mexico 'steps from the beach' take a look inside G #makeit'.

node.text:
In 2006, Janet Blaser packed her bags and moved from Santa Cruz, California to Mazatlán, Mexico to start her own business (and eventually retire). 🌴⁠
⁠
Earlier this year, she relocated to a two-bedroom, 1,100-square-foot apartment with 10-foot ceilings, just a few minutes from one of her favorite beaches. The rent is $420 per month, not including utilities. 🤯⁠
⁠
For more on how Janet found her rental, plus what she spends each month, check out the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 09, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, outdoors and text that says 'Yale's 'most popular class ever' is available for free online make'.

node.text: The New York Times called it the university’s “most popular class ever” — and the hundreds of people who reported life-changing improvements after taking the class were enough to convince a CNBC Make It contributor. ⁠Read more about his experience, plus details on how to sign up for the class yourself, in the link in bio.⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 09, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'The interview question that makes a job seeker stand out, according to LinkedIn's VP of global hiring #makeit'.

node.text:
Recruiters are on a tear to fill a growing number of open roles as the U.S. hiring market rebounds this summer. ⁠
⁠
But remember, job interviews are a two-way street and you can ask questions to make sure the company and the job are what you're looking for, too. ⁠
⁠
At the link in our bio, LinkedIn's VP of global hiring shares the top question that often sets job seekers apart.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 09, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Bad at public speaking? Use this mental trick that takes just 15 minutes, says speech expert #make'.

node.text:
Speech anxiety is one of the most common social fears, affecting 15% to 30% of the general population.⁠
⁠
But improving your public speaking skills has nothing to do with changing your personality or your emotions — and everything to do with understanding how people listen.⁠
⁠
At the link in our bio, we're sharing 5 tips from a speech expert, and what to remember when imagining yourself as the audience.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 09, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, office and text that says 'Deciding between a traditional or a Roth 401(k)? Here's what to consider #makeit'.

node.text:
When saving for retirement, investing in either a traditional 401(k) or a Roth 401(k) is a smart idea if your employer offers one. But they aren’t exactly the same. Each type comes with its own pros and cons.⁠
⁠
We're breaking down the major differences at the link in our bio. ✍️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
A new study from LinkedIn sheds some light on how long it *really* takes to get hired. 🧐⁠
⁠
From finance to engineering, check out the link in our bio to learn more about the jobs that take the longest time to fill across 15 different industries.
